          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
          Trump chooses diplomacy
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/trump-closes-diplomacy-iran-israel-strikes.png" alt="Trump administration closes diplomacy over war with Iran but Israel continues strikes." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Benjamin Netanyahu signs a guest book at the White House in Washington DC, April 7, 2025. Source: Avi Ohayon/GPO</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Trump rejected Israeli PM Netanyahu‚Äôs push for a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-18-04-2025-h1-1-joint-strike?source=weebsite" target="_blank">joint strike</a> on Iranian nuclear facilities, opting instead to pursue diplomacy. Israel had developed detailed plans to strike as early as May, involving commando raids and a broader bombing campaign, but these required US support to be viable.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          While some American officials were open to the idea, others, including JD Vance and Intelligence Director Tulsi Gabbard, warned of the risk of sparking a broader war. Trump‚Äôs administration instead began negotiations with Tehran, giving the country a few months to agree on limits to its nuclear program.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Simultaneously, Israel‚Äôs 2023 operations in Syria intensified, with at least <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-18-04-2025-h1-2-40-strikes-on-Iranian-militias?source=weebsite" target="_blank">40 strikes on Iranian militias</a>, Hezbollah, and weapons facilities across the country, aiming to counter Iran‚Äôs expanding presence and prevent Syria from becoming a launchpad for attacks. Targets included airports, command centers, and drone assembly facilities. Israel‚Äôs approach shows a preference for precision strikes and covert operations to delay Iran‚Äôs nuclear capabilities while avoiding full-scale war.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
