        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Bangladesh‚Äôs rising extremism</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/bangladesh-rising-islamic-extremism.png" alt="Bangladesh is facing a dangerous rise in Islamist radicalization under Muhammad Yunus‚Äôs interim government" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Activists in Dhaka protest the attack on the Bangladesh Assistant High Commission in Agartala, India. Source: Rakibul Hasan Rafiu/NurPhoto via Getty Images</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Under PM Sheikh Hasina‚Äôs secular leadership, Bangladesh preserved <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-18-04-2025-h2-1-relative-stability?source=weebsite" target="_blank">relative stability</a> and protected its Hindu minority from Islamist extremism. Hasina‚Äôs government banned radical groups and arrested extremist leaders, and upheld secular values in governance and law. However, since her ouster in August 2024 and the rise of Muhammad Yunus‚Äôs interim regime, Islamic radicalism has resurged dramatically.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Previously banned militant groups are currently operating freely, with convicted terrorists released and public rallies <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-18-04-2025-h2-2-calling-for-an-Islamic-caliphate?source=weebsite" target="_blank">calling for an Islamic caliphate</a>.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Attacks on Hindus, including burning of homes, destruction of temples, and mob violence, have sharply increased, with over 2,200 reported incidents in 2024 alone. The Yunus government has dismissed such violence as ‚Äúpolitically motivated‚Äù or exaggerated. With secular protections dismantled, Bangladesh faces an existential threat to its pluralist foundation. Observers warn the country risks becoming a hub for Islamist extremism, undermining decades of progress under Hasina‚Äôs leadership.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
