        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Make the West great again</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: Trump meets Italian PM Giorgia Meloni, says he is 100% confident on Europe trade agreement.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          On Thursday afternoon, President Trump met with Italian PM Giorgia Meloni. Many might label this as the EU's charm offensive aimed at persuading the US to ease some tariffs and support Ukraine. When asked about the EU's potential tariffs, Meloni <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-18-04-2025-h3-1-expressed-confidence?source=weebsite" target="_blank">expressed confidence</a> in a trade pact between the US and the European Union.
        </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Trump expressed optimism about a future EU-US trade arrangement but said there‚Äôs ‚Äúno rush,‚Äù welcoming expected tariff revenues. Despite previously criticizing the tariffs, Meloni called the US a ‚Äúreliable partner‚Äù and stressed unity. Their ideological alignment positions her as a mediator between Washington and Brussels. Trump praised Meloni‚Äôs leadership, while she remained hopeful for an agreement before the 90-day tariff suspension ends.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Meloni also invited Trump to visit Italy, and he accepted with pleasure. Trump plans to meet other European leaders during this trip. Speaking at the White House, Meloni highlighted their shared political values and expressed a desire for stronger US-EU cooperation. ‚ÄúThe goal for me is to make the West great again, and I think together we can do that,‚Äù she said.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">As leader of Italy‚Äôs right-wing Brothers of Italy party, Meloni may be able to leverage her political similarities with Trump to influence discussions and move negotiations forward.</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
