          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Who were the Khmer Rouge?
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/who-were-the-khmer-rouge.png" alt="A line of Khmer Rouge soldiers walking through a forested area during the Cambodian Civil War." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Pol Pot leading Khmer Rouge fighters. Source: AP Photo/Kyodo</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">    
           Thursday marked the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-18-04-2025-f1-1-50th-anniversary-of-the-takeover?source=weebsite" target="_blank">50th anniversary of the takeover</a> of the Khmer Rouge in Cambodia. Its legacy leaves a dark shadow on Cambodian history. The Khmer Rouge was a dictatorial regime that lasted from 1975 until 1979, with Pol Pot as the leader. The regime aimed to be a classless and agrarian society. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Before the takeover, Cambodia was ambushed by spillovers of the Vietnam War and suffered from US bombings, of which Henry Kissinger was the architect. The earlier government was seen as weak. Many rural Cambodians were tired of the situation and supported the Khmer Rouge out of a combination of fear and hope.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The regime didn't alleviate the Cambodian struggles.
          </p>
          <ul style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.6;padding-left:16px;">
          <li>The educated or anyone who seemed to question their authority were the first to be imprisoned, tortured, and murdered.
          </li>
              <li>Cties and schools were banned.
          </li>
              <li>People were thrown into labor camps.
          </li>
            <li>Everything was banned, including money.
          </li>
            <li>The regime's policies led to the death of 2 million Cambodians, a third of the overall population. 
          </li>
          </ul>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">It was one of the worst genocides in the 20th century, and one of the more overlooked ones. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The Vietnamese overthrew the regime; Pol Pot escaped into the jungles, shielded by his supporters. Pol Pot allegedly succumbed to a heart attack in 1998 and didn‚Äôt face a day in court. A UN-backed tribunal convicted a few leaders, but many former Khmer Rouge members remain unpunished.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
